HEADWORD: Pirl
<hw>Pirl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Purl</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To spin, as a top.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To twist or twine, as hair in making fishing
lines.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pirn</ent>⟦br⟧
